[2] China (Hong Kong, SAR)
Date: Fri, 6 Jan 2006 07:34:48 -0500 (EST)
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: News.gov.hk, Hong Kong, 6 Jan 2006 [edited]
<http://www.news.gov.hk/en/category/healthandcommunity/060106/html/060106en05007.htm>

The Centre for Health Protection has confirmed the 1st imported case
of Dengue fever this year [2006].
The patient is a 45-year-old man who developed fever, headache, and
muscle and joint pain on December 22 [2005]. He is receiving
treatment in Princess Margaret Hospital and in stable condition. He
had travelled to the Mainland and Indonesia from 8 to 22 Dec 2005.
His home contacts did not have any symptoms.
The Centre urges people to guard against the disease and prevent
mosquito breeding.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
