[3] Mexico (Oaxaca)
Date: Mon, 02 Jan 2006 10:19:33 +0100
From: Alfonso J. Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Yahoo Noticias, Mexico, 30 Dec 2005 [trans. Jorge
Gonzalez-Mendoza; edited]
<http://mx.news.yahoo.com/051230/26/1l1uf.html>

Health Services in the Mexican state of Oaxaca registered in [2005]
1076 cases of dengue fever; 910 were classic dengue fever and 166
were hemorrhagic dengue fever [DHF]. However, no deaths were reported.
In spite of heavy rainfalls and severe damage caused by hurricanes,
particularly Stan, authorities affirmed that no pandemics of the
disease occurred, since people responded to prevention campaigns
launched this year [2005].
They explained that until the 51st Epidemiological Week [of 2005],
Oaxaca Health Services had 1076 cases of dengue fever registered; 536
occurred in Tehuantepec isthmus, where 441 cases of classic dengue
and 93 cases of hemorrhagic dengue fever were recorded.
They added that even though meteorological phenomena such as
hurricane Stan severely affected the area, this did not lead to a
huge increase in the number of cases of dengue fever, as was the case
in Veracruz. On the contrary, they said, the case toll remained stable.
Authorities explained that community participation in the fight
against the _Aedes aegypti_ mosquito vector, through cleaning their
households' backyards and roofs, was fruitful, since no deaths cause
by dengue had been recorded.
In order to fight the insect, they reported that in August 2005, 5
million Pesos [USD 472 144] were allocated for purchasing materials,
and during the contingency provoked by Hurricane Stan, healthcare
worker teams were sent to [the] affected areas, such as Tuxtepec,
Istmo, and Costa.
Antivectorial control has been expanded to 489 communities in 166
municipalities, and 31 209 hectares of land and 411 868 households
had been treated.
Health authorities pointed out that, even though temperatures have
recently fallen, Health Services are in a permanent state of alert.
According to official figures, of the 1076 cases of dengue fever
recorded in Oaxaca during 2005, 536 were found in the Tehuantepec
Isthmus, followed by Tuxtepec with 263 cases, 233 of which correspond
to classic dengue fever and 30 to the hemorrhagic form [DHF] of the disease.
The coastal region had 136 dengue fever cases; 107 were classic
dengue fever and 29 DHF. Central valleys had 78 cases (69 and 9,
respectively); Mixteca, 40 cases (36 and 4), and the highlands
reported 23 cases of dengue fever (22 and 1, respectively).
